description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a full time Nursing Assistant to join the nursing team in the Skin Service Outpatient departments at Salisbury NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will be based predominately within Plastic Surgery Outpatients to support and contribute to the organisation and support of Consultant led clinics and minor op theatre lists, treatments and follow up aftercare within a busy and demanding environment which provides quality, patient-focused care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, the post holder will be prepared to work collaboratively with all services including, where needed, working in differing outpatient departments within the same/current job role but differing specialities areas outside of your speciality at times of need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome applications from individuals who have a genuine interest in outpatient nursing who are motivated and are an enthusiastic individual committed to providing excellent patient care. You must be experienced in working within a team structure and possess excellent time management and organisation skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will need to have excellent communication skills – in particular listening skills, as well as having a friendly, open, empathetic and compassionate communication style. You will need a strong ability to engage with patients, visitors and colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience within a health care setting is essential, preferably within primary care with a secondary education qualification in numeracy and literacy. It would be advantageous if the successful applicant has experience in an outpatient setting however full training will be given to be competent to undertake the duties necessary for this role. An NVQ/QCF in Health and Social Care would be essential for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements of the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside the Skin Service team in the day to day running of clinics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Addressing patient queries effectively to offer support and reassurance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean, prepare and assemble of associated surgical equipment prior to and during treatment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as minor ops runner/escort&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare all areas prior to any clinical activities ensuring equipment is checked ready for use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure equipment is stored correctly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with stock control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must be IT literate and have the ability to work without direct supervision after a period of supervision and training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post is flexible, and the post holder will therefore, be required to provide support over a wide range of service/functions. Key to this flexibility is the requirement for staff to work variable days on a week by week basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our friendly and supportive team, committed to staff development, you will have the opportunity to develop both professionally and personally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suzy Rainbow&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister&lt;/p&gt;
